rComments: Professor Baqir is one of the most kind professors at uOttawa! He is so incredibly knowledgable and experienced and genuinely cares about his students. Although you might be a little confused at the beginning of the class with his expectations, he really just wants what's best for students and will always try to give you the best grade possible!

Lots of people did not enjoy prof. Baqir's class but I loved it. If you put in the effort to doing the readings and participate in class, you will get out what you put in. Granted the prof is soft spoken but he is brilliant if you listen to what he has to say. I think most people had a bad experience due to the TA in our class, not the prof.

Very caring professor who is happy to provide necessary help to his students. Very knowledeagble and professional in development studies. I was so inspired by him and the readings he assigned. However, he can be a little disorgnized sometimes. It takes extremely long to get back your mideterm grade. His TA is so annoyed and a hard marker.
